Richard Schulze



Richard M. Schulze
Founder and Chairman Emeritus – Best Buy
Chairman and President – Olympus Ventures, LLC
Richard M. Schulze was born in St. Paul, Minnesota in 1941, and has lived in the Twin Cities area all his life. He began his working life at the age of eleven as a paperboy and held a series of jobs through high school. Although he had long dreamed of attending college and had planned to attend The College of St. Thomas, military service put him on a different path. (Dick now holds an honorary doctorate from University of St. Thomas and the University of Minnesota.) 
After working with his father for several years as a manufacturer’s representative for electronics components, Dick founded his own company in 1966, The Sound of Music, offering audio components, sheet music, records and tapes, and musical instruments, and had expanded to nine stores in Minnesota by 1983.
In the early 1980s, the consumer electronics business and retailing industry underwent rapid change with the rise of big box retailers and everyday-low-price chains. Recognizing that small music outlets could not survive, Dick reinvented his business, renamed it Best Buy, adopted a customer friendly format, and expanded its product offerings.
Dick serves as Founder and Chairman Emeritus of Best Buy; he previously served as CEO until June of 2002, when he became chair of the board. Today, Best Buy operates more than 1,400 stores in the U.S. and 479 stores in Canada, China and Mexico; employing more than 145,000 people worldwide.
Although he now divides his time between Minnesota and Florida, Dick remains deeply committed to his home state. He helped establish the Schulze School of Entrepreneurship at the University of St. Thomas (UST) in St. Paul. He is a member of the Minnesota Business Partnership, a collective of the state’s 85 largest corporations, which works alongside legislators to develop public policy. He also serves on the Board of Trustees of UST and is Chairman of the Opus College of Business in Minneapolis.
In addition to his work with the University of St. Thomas, Dick has been involved with the Mayo Clinic and the United Way. Propelled by concern for the welfare of one of his children who lives with diabetes, Dick has worked with The Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation and been instrumental in supporting and helping to develop a comprehensive program with the University of Minnesota, whose goal is to eradicate the disease. After Dick’s wife Sandra passed away from a rare cancer in 2001, Schulze helped to establish the American Cancer Society Hope Lodges, homes-away-from-home for individuals undergoing cancer treatment.
The Richard M. Schulze Family Foundation was established in 2004 to fulfill the Schulze’s desire to extend the reach of their charitable work. The Foundation supports organizations that improve the lives of families and children in the areas of education, human services, medical-related human services, and camps.
Dick currently serves as the Chairman and President of Olympus Ventures, LLC, the President and Director of Founders Properties, LLC. He is also Founder and President of Best Jets International, a charter aircraft company which operates out of Minneapolis, Minnesota. He serves as a member on the board of the Richard M. Schulze Family Foundation. He’s married to Maureen and has ten children and twenty nine grandchildren which is the most meaningful part of his life.
Watch Mr. Schulze’s highlight video.




