amount
paid to Phoenix during fiscal 2009 was $18 million. 
Susan
S. Hoff, Mr. Schulze's daughter, is Chairperson, President and Chief Executive Officer of The Best Buy Children's Foundation, for which she has served as principal executive officer since
the inception of the foundation. In addition, since October 2007, Ms. Hoff has served as a Vice President of our company. Ms. Hoff's base salary was set in fiscal 2009 at $233,000 and
she was eligible for a short-term incentive award, payable in cash, expressed as 45% of her base salary. During fiscal 2009, Ms. Hoff received $232,000 in total cash compensation.
Also during fiscal 2009, Ms. Hoff was awarded options to purchase 12,000 shares of Best Buy common stock at an exercise price of $41.19 per share and options to purchase 12,000 shares of Best
Buy common stock at an exercise price of $26.88 per share. The stock options expire in August 2018 and October 2018, respectively, and vest ratably over four years. Ms. Hoff's compensation was
deemed reasonable by the Compensation Committee based upon the responsibilities encompassed by her role. 
