and approved the leases (with Mr. Schulze not voting). The Board relied on one or more of its members who had no financial interest in the properties to review market comparisons,
look into alternative rental agreements and negotiate with Mr. Schulze. The Board determined that these real estate leases were in our best interest and had terms that are competitive with
terms available from unaffiliated third parties. Real estate lease renewals will be reviewed by the Audit Committee pursuant to our Related-Party Transactions Policy. 
